We solve this problem using bottom-up approach where we iterate over all possible sums up-to sum(k) starting from zero and check if it's achievable or not by finding the maximum value at each index i which adds upto jth sum. We keep track of previously calculated values so as to avoid recomputations and use memoization technique to store our results. Our base case would be when sum(i)=nums[i]. After iterating through entire array, we return whether sum(k) was achieved or not.

